<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[701,1212,694,1749]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.—Mesonotum black with axillae and metanotum white; abdominal segment 1–6 mostly orange with white spots laterally on segments 1, 2, 5, 6. Sheath short, about 2X longer than broad.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="141" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[701,1212,694,1749]" lastBlockId="6.[159,670,196,719]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="141" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">
Description.—Female (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1101,860,885]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[140,186,1372,1392]" captionTargetBox="[111,1159,196,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[111,1159,196,1339]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 11–15. Hyperxiphia semilutea. 11, Lateral. 12, Thorax, lateral. 13, Thorax, dorsal. 14, Head, front. 15, Head, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3728045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3728045/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
): Length 
<quantity box="[701,826,893,918]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.31" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" unit="mm" value="13.1">13.1 mm</quantity>
. Antenna black. Head black with orbits (except upper) and area below antennae yellow. Thorax black, yellow on: pronotum (black spot in middle), spot anterior to mesepisternum, spot posterior to each lateral lobe, metascutellum. Legs with coxae and trochanters yellow, femora black, fore and mid tibiae yellow, hind tibia yellow with apex black; tarsi with basitarsi yellow, rest black. Abdomen with tergite 1 and laterally on tergite 2 yellow, tergites 3–6 orange, 5 and 6 laterally yellow; 7th black, 8th yellow spot laterally, 9 apically yellow, 10 yellow. Wings hyaline, veins and stigma black. 
<emphasis box="[877,944,1392,1416]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[963,1116,1392,1417]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[140,186,1372,1392]" captionTargetBox="[111,1159,196,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[111,1159,196,1339]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 11–15. Hyperxiphia semilutea. 11, Lateral. 12, Thorax, lateral. 13, Thorax, dorsal. 14, Head, front. 15, Head, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3728045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3728045/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Figs. 14, 15</figureCitation>
): Frons with longitudinal carinae from level of hind ocelli through supraclypeal area. Antennae with ~18 antennomeres. Labial palpus with 4 palpomeres, maxillary palpus with 4 palpomeres; first palpomere about as long as remaining palpomeres combined; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1038,1059,1618,1634]" fontSize="7" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">rd</superScript>
palpomere very short; apical palpomere clublike. Eyes slightly diverging below, lower interocular distance about 1.2X eye height. Head from above short behind eyes, distance behind eyes slightly shorter than eye length. 
<emphasis box="[263,352,1525,1549]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[375,536,1524,1549]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[140,186,1372,1392]" captionTargetBox="[111,1159,196,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[111,1159,196,1339]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 11–15. Hyperxiphia semilutea. 11, Lateral. 12, Thorax, lateral. 13, Thorax, dorsal. 14, Head, front. 15, Head, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3728045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3728045/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Figs. 12, 13</figureCitation>
): Propleuron shiny, few punctures mostly ventrally. Pronotum shiny, diagonal area of short carinae at center. Mesonotum, metanotum rugulose; shiny less punctate areas on outer lateral lobes and apex of mesoscutellum; downturned sides of mesoscutellum shiny. Mesopleuron shiny with punctures, punctures separated by interspaces equal to or more than puncture diameters; mesosternum shiny, without punctures; mesepimeron with fine cross carinae, metapleuron rugulose. Hind basitarsus slightly shorter than remaining tarsomeres combined. 
<emphasis box="[1035,1152,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Sheath (
<figureCitation box="[755,847,1724,1749]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[140,186,1372,1392]" captionTargetBox="[111,1159,196,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[111,1159,196,1339]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 11–15. Hyperxiphia semilutea. 11, Lateral. 12, Thorax, lateral. 13, Thorax, dorsal. 14, Head, front. 15, Head, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3728045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3728045/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) short, about 2X longer than broad, subequal in length to basal plates.
</paragraph>
