<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="141" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[159,670,196,719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="141">Etymology.—Name is based on the partly orange abdomen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="141" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[159,670,196,719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="141">Remarks.—The yellow orbits, upper and lower margins of the pronotum, axillae, metanotum, and fifth, sixth, and apical segments of the abdomen will distinguish this species. The diverging eyes below and short sheath are also helpful.</paragraph>
